      "type": "markdown",
      "title": "What is a Website?",
      "content": "# Real-Life Story: Building a Toy Shop\n\nImagine you want to open a **small toy shop**.\n\nYour shop needs:\n\n- A **board** with shop name\n- Toys arranged nicely\n- Someone to open the door and talk to customers\n\nA **website works the same way**.\n\n---\n\n## Three Important Parts of a Website\n\n1. **HTML** â€“ Structure (like walls and shelves)\n2. **CSS** â€“ Style (colors, size, beauty)\n3. **JavaScript** â€“ Brain (actions and logic)\n\nWithout these three, a website cannot work.\n\n---\n\n## Simple Rule\n\n- HTML shows **what is there**\n- CSS shows **how it looks**\n- JavaScript shows **how it behaves**\n\nNext, letâ€™s understand them one by one.",
      "video": {
        "videoUrl": "/public/web-basics.mp4",
        "title": "Website Basics Explained",
        "duration": "4:10",
        "autoShow": true
      }
    },

    "positive": {
      "type": "interactive-code",
      "title": "Positive Case: Simple Web Page",
      "description": "This is a very small web page using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.",
      "code": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <style>\n      h1 { color: blue; }\n      button { padding: 10px; }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <h1>My Toy Shop</h1>\n    <button onclick=\"sayHello()\">Click Me</button>\n\n    <script>\n      function sayHello() {\n        alert('Welcome to my shop');\n      }\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>",
      "showPreview": true,
      "explanation": "**How this works:**\n\n- `<h1>` is HTML (structure)\n- `color: blue` is CSS (style)\n- `onclick` is JavaScript (action)\n\nAll three work together like a team."
    },

